  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-8 clean, bounded envelope)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors scoped-out or not-applicable (acceptable at MRL 2). Operating envelope explicitly bounded (flow rate 1–7 L/min, rotational speed 1500–3500 RPM, five impeller geometry tolerance variants ±0.05 mm). Validation sampling is honest about coverage: three of five operating points have experimental hemolysis data; the remaining two are covered by CFD-only sensitivity sweeps with documented uncertainty. This package is structurally complete and clean; no weakener should fire.",
